Foot and mouth disease, Israel
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 21 Jun 2011 from Dr Michel
Bellaiche, director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry
of Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 4
Start date: 17 Apr 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 27 Apr 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Mar 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic),
laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Kabul, Acco, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jun 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep, goats / 250 / 20 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: high fever and limping in sheep. No clinical
signs in goats.

Outbreak 2: Qela (Gonen), Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 16 Jun 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 250 / 7 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: free-ranging herd. 7 cows show clinical signs as
salivation and limping.

Outbreak 3: Moawyye, Hadera, Haifa
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Jun 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 53 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep, goats 48 / 8 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: the herd is a mixed herd with sheep (38), goats
(10), and beef cattle (53). Clinical signs were seen only in 8 lambs
aged 3-5 months. These lambs were not vaccinated before the outbreak.
One calf showed lesions in the mouth. No signs were seen in goats.

Outbreak 4: Ben Ammi, Acco, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Jun 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 295 / 16 / 1 / 0 / 0

Affected population: salivation, limping. Beef cattle. Clinical
suspicion.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 4
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep, goats / 298 / 28 / 0 / 0 / 0
Cattle / 598 / 24 / 1 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or
inconclusive
illegal movement of animals

Epidemiological comments: most of the affected herds were vaccinated
within the last year.

Ten of the outbreaks have been typed and found as due to type O.

The herds which have not been typed yet are Majdal Shams and Rahat.
Ben Ammi and Qela are suspected.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, movement control inside the country,
zoning, vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), no treatment of
affected animals

Measures to be applied: screening, disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Kimron Veterinary Institute (National
laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 03 Jun 2011 / Positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 03 Jun 2011 / Positive
Cattle / virus isolation / 03 Jun 2011 / Positive
Sheep, goats / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 15 Jun 2011 / Positive
Sheep, goats / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 19 Jun 2011 / Positive

